def: The sound made when a cork is forcibly drawn from a bottle."The cloop of a cork wrenched from a bottle." Thackeray.
The ratio of the three crystallographic axes which determinesthe position of any plane; also, the fundamental axial ratio for agiven species.
A tribe of North American Indians who originally occupied theregion about Green Bay, Lake Michigan, but were driven back from thelake and nearly exterminated in 1640 by the IIlinnois.
A man who wears an apron; a laboring man; a mechanic. [Obs.]Shak.
The act of announcing or proclaiming beforehand. [Obs.]
A group of Coleoptera having a snoutlike head; the snoutbeetles, curculios, or weevils.
To impress with terror; to coerce by intimidation.Humiliated by the tyranny of foreign despotism, and terrorized byecclesiastical authority. J. A. Symonds.
Quality of being customable; conformity to custom. [Obs.]
